nglish <i>fleming</i>. The word reflects a Norman French form of Old French <i>flamanc</i> ‘Fleming’, from the stem <i>flam-</i> + the ancient Germanic suffix <i>-ing</i>. In the Middle Ages there was considerable commercial intercourse between England and the Netherlands, particularly in the wool trade, and many Flemish weavers and dyers settled in England. This surname is also common in south and east Scotland and in Ireland, where it is sometimes found in the Gaelicized form <b>Pléamonn</b>.","German: variant of   Flemming  , cognate with 1 above."],"variants":[{"name":"Flemings","meanings":["English: plural form of   Fleming  .","Americanized form of Flemish <b>Vleminckx</b>: patronymic from <b>Vleminck</b>, an ethnic name for someone from Flanders, Middle Dutch <i>vleminc</i>."]},{"name":"Flanders","meanings":["English: ethnic name from Middle English <i>Fla(u)ndres</i> ‘Flanders’, denoting someone from Flanders, a historical region covering parts of modern-day Belgium, France, and the Netherlands. Compare   Fleming  ."]},{"name":"Fleeman","meanings":["English: variant of   Fleming  ."]},{"name":"Flemming","meanings":["German: ethnic name for someone from Flanders, Middle High German <i>vlaeminc</i>. People from Flanders spread throughout Germany, as well as England, in the Middle Ages as clothmakers and dyers.","English: variant of   Fleming  ."]},{"name":"Flamenco","meanings":["Spanish: ethnic name from <i>flamenco</i> ‘Fleming, Flemish person’ (see   Fleming  )."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Fleming I was born about 1300, in Wath upon Dearne, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of John Fleming II and Isabella de la Mare. He had at least 2 sons. He died about 1360, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 62."},"et":{"Abt 1300–Abt 1360":"umbes 1300–umbes 1360","1300–1360":"1300–1360","–Male":"Surnud","1320–1364":"1320–1364","1332–1412":"1332–1412","1275–1351":"1275–1351","–1356":"–1356","1275":"1275","1351":"1351","1360":"1360","after 1356, widow":"pärast 1356","Bef 1351":"enne 1351","Abt 1360":"umbes 1360","1412":"1412","Abt 1300":"umbes 1300","1356":"1356","1300":"1300","1332":"1332","1364":"1364","1320":"1320","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Croston, Lancashire, England":"Croston, Lancashire, England","Wath upon Dearne, Yorkshire, England":"Wath upon Dearne, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1300–Abt 1360":"noin 1300–noin 1360","1300–1360":"1300–1360","–Male":"Kuollut","1320–1364":"1320–1364","1332–1412":"1332–1412","1275–1351":"1275–1351","–1356":"–1356","1275":"1275","1351":"1351","1360":"1360","after 1356, widow":"1356 jälkeen","Bef 1351":"ennen vuotta 1351","Abt 1360":"noin 1360","1412":"1412","Abt 1300":"noin 1300","1356":"1356","1300":"1300","1332":"1332","1364":"1364","1320":"1320","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Croston, Lancashire, England":"Croston, Lancashire, England","Wath upon Dearne, Yorkshire, England":"Wath upon Dearne, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1300–Abt 1360":"environ 1300–environ 1360","1300–1360":"1300–1360","–Male":"Décédé","1320–1364":"1320–1364","1332–1412":"1332–1412","1275–1351":"1275–1351","–1356":"–1356","1275":"1275","1351":"1351","1360":"1360","after 1356, widow":"après 1356","Bef 1351":"avant 1351","Abt 1360":"environ 1360","1412":"1412","Abt 1300":"environ 1300","1356":"1356","1300":"1300","1332":"1332","1364":"1364","1320":"1320"